channel.title: Javadoc Problems [SOLVED]
channel.description:
Hello, I'm trying to document the 317 client, but for some reason alot of the classes are just being skipped over when generating the html file. All the files are loaded, but it doesn't generate the html file for some, like classes 30_Sub1, 5, 7, 8, 46, 43, 47. What could be causeing it to skip over those files?
EDIT: Fixed the problem. Those classes it skipped were just final classes, not public final classes. Just used -private and it worked.

item.title: Javadoc Problems [SOLVED]
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

oksuper_:

They are most likely not public, and therefore not included in the to-doc list. Simply run javadoc with the -private flag.

Thanks super_.
